---
title: Melty Mushroom Ravioli with Truffle Cream Sauce plus Kale & Walnuts
description: This mushroom ravioli bake feels luxurious, with garlicky cream sauce, truffle zest, tender kale, and earthy crushed walnuts. But since you’ll cook the ravioli, sauce, and greens all together in our oven-ready tray, this delicious dish couldn’t be easier to assemble. The best part? Toss the tray when you're done for practically no cleanup!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67325a7f1cd01ca44ffc2bce-8f3319da.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67325a7f1cd01ca44ffc2bce-en-US.pdf
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 530 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 17 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1210 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/melty-mushroom-ravioli-67325a7f1cd01ca44ffc2bce
author: Sara Heilman
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Gently separate @mushroom ravioli{9%ounce}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}.

In #oven-ready tray{1}, mix together @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and as much @truffle seasoning{2%g} as you like until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, divide between two trays.

Stir in @water{1/3%cup}. Add ravioli and stir until evenly coated.

> For 4 servings, divide ravioli between two trays.

Top ravioli mixture with kale.

> TIP: Spread the kale out, making sure no leaves hang over the edges of your tray!

Cover tray tightly with #foil{}; bake on middle rack until ravioli are al dente, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, lightly crush @walnuts{1/2%ounce} in their bag using the bottom of a #mug{}.

Carefully remove foil from tray. Stir mushroom ravioli bake until kale is incorporated and everything is coated in sauce. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide ravioli bake between plates. Sprinkle with walnuts and serve.